mate’s thoughts seemed theirs; they raised a half mutinous cry. But dashing 
the rattling lightning links to the deck, and snatching the burning harpoon, 
Ahab waved it like a torch among them; swearing to transfix with it the first 
sailor that but cast loose a rope’s end. Petrified by his aspect, and still 
more shrinking from the fiery dart that he held, the men fell back in dismay, 
